As former Delaware Deputy Secretary of Health and Social Services and a supporter of strong federal funding for the Title X program, it’s imperative that we continue to give family planning clinics the tools they need and remove the barriers women face in accessing contraception.

Highlighting Delaware’s innovative work, the @nytimes recently featured the strides our state is making in improving access to birth control and reducing the number of unplanned pregnancies at Title X family planning clinics.

As the nation’s dedicated source of funding for family planning, Title X helps health centers in Delaware and across the country provide low or no cost contraceptives to women and their families so they can take full control of their reproductive health. https://www.nytimes.com/2018/12/18/upshot/set-it-and-forget-it-how-better-contraception-could-be-a-secret-to-reducing-poverty.html?fbclid=IwAR0K5SIFDrcSSfe2qYWN1DSP6OkUMiWo6NewPAkMjwxfVbCSKhe_8Pnh70w …
